# WHAT: Template for required environment variables. Copy to .env (gitignored).
# WHY:  Never commit real API keys (OWASP A02/A05, secrets-management).
# HOW:  Fireworks AI issues one API key per account; models are selected by ID.
#
# TROUBLESHOOTING (verified 2026-07-11): Fireworks' inference API returns
# HTTP 404 "Model not found, inaccessible, and/or not deployed" for BOTH an
# invalid/expired/missing FIREWORKS_API_KEY and a genuinely bad model ID —
# it does not distinguish auth failures from bad model IDs in the response.
# If every model call 404s (including well-known models like
# llama-v3p1-70b-instruct), the API key is invalid/revoked — check that
# first before assuming a model ID typo. See README.md Troubleshooting.

FIREWORKS_API_KEY=
FIREWORKS_BASE_URL=https://api.fireworks.ai/inference/v1

# Model routing (Section 12.3 Model Routing Layer pattern) — override per agent.
FIREWORKS_MODEL_ORCHESTRATOR=accounts/fireworks/models/llama-v3p1-70b-instruct
FIREWORKS_MODEL_SPECIALIST=accounts/fireworks/models/qwen2p5-coder-32b-instruct
FIREWORKS_MODEL_RESEARCH=accounts/fireworks/models/deepseek-v3p1

# Local fallback (never assume single-provider availability)
LOCAL_LLAMA_TOOLS_URL=http://localhost:8009
LOCAL_LLAMA_CHAT_URL=http://localhost:8011
